			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Just played WoW.<a name="57155"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 17 04 2:48 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I am a beta tester for WoW, and I've been one for several months now.
<br />

<br />
Unfortunately, there is no Bard class in WoW, and so I tried many of the classes to find one that I could enjoy.  I have tried the Warlock, Rogue, Druid, and Shaman classes.
<br />

<br />
I simply cannot enjoy WoW, and will not buy it when it is released.  I have posted probably upwards of 100 posts on the WoW boards in regards to the problems with the game, so it will be difficult to summarize in this one post, but I'll do my best.
<br />

<br />
- There are too few classes in WoW, and they overlap too much.  There are very few compelling spells/skills that only one class has.  For example, mages and rogues can both go invis; warriors, paladins, druids (!) and maybe others can tank; almost all casting classes have nukes (mages are best); shamans, druids, paladins, priests can heal.  There is just too much cross-over and a great lack of special abilities.  Cross-over of abilities can be alright, as long as there are several class-defining awe-inspiring abilities for each class -- there are very very few of these.
<br />

<br />
- There is little to look forward to in each class.  Once you get your basic spells/skills, you almost NEVER get new interesting skills at higher levels.  You only get upgraded versions of your current abilities.  For example, as a Shaman you get an instant-cast nuke, a DoT, a weapon buff, totems, and a heal.  You don't get something new and exciting at higher levels, you get level 2, 3, 4 nuke, 2, 3, 4 Dot, 2, 3, 4 weapon buff, 2, 3, 4, totems, 2, 3, 4, heals.  It's not like in EQ1 where you have some great new type of spells to look forward to.  What's worse, even though you get these more powerful versions of the same spells over and over, the monsters get more hp, so you may as well just have the same spell!  It grows stagnant.
<br />

<br />
- There is no extended character customization.  You cannot customize your facial features at all (you just choose a face), you cannot customize your size at all, no tattoos, nothing.  Lots of people are complaining about this problem.
<br />

<br />
- It is IMPOSSIBLE to own any equipment you could call &quot;uber&quot; at any level other than the max level.  *ALL* items either have a min-level or are soulbound (no-drop).  The min-levels are set such that at any given level (other than max level), you have only a handful of different gear choices, and they are all very similar in power.  Staggeringly similar in power!  For example, a very good staff for a level 15 will only be perhaps 5 dps better than a mediocre weapon.  It's not possible to awe people with your great gear.  Gear is inconsequential really.
<br />

<br />
- The questing system has potential, but lacks variety.  50% of all quests are &quot;gather X&quot; quests.  The rest are &quot;retrieve this item&quot; or &quot;kill this guy&quot; quests.  They could have done so much more with this.
<br />

<br />
I am tired of the game, and unless they make some major changes, I won't play it when it comes out.
<br />

<br />
EQ2 looks much more promising IMHO, I can't wait for it to be released.
<br />

<br />
- Mirthe
<br />
64 Bard
<br />
Quellious
<br />
</span></td>
