			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Just played WoW.<a name="57180"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 17 04 5:50 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I have been Beta testing for a few months as well and while you are free to your own opinion I have to disagree with most of your points.
<br />

<br />
There are significant differances between classes.  For instance the three Tank classes you mentioned, the Warrior builds rage as the fight goes along, which he can expend to do special maneuvers, plus he has three different stances which come with different abilities so he goes from being a defensive tank to DPS to a decent soloer.
<br />

<br />
The Paladin (probably the most boring class in combat) usually soften up his opponents with a quick crusaders strike and then lowers the boom with Holy Strike.  He can play with hate with his insta casting short duration seals, either increasing or decreasing hate on himself or others among othere things and then he has his auras, mana free boons that effect the entire party that he can only have one on at a time and range from mana regen to Armor boosts.
<br />

<br />
Then finally the druids bear from.  You can change into a friggin bear and tank.  You lose the ability to cast spells but gain the ability to get rage and expend it to use powers (that are different than the warriors)
<br />

<br />
If those aren't different abilities I am not sure what are.  There is more difference in characters than in EQ, perhaps what you are confusing here is that they are not as dependent on each other as EQ is.
<br />

<br />
Character customization is better than EQ (choosing face, skin tone, hair color, hair style and &quot;facial&quot; hair (which is jewelry and other things like tatoos as well)), but not as good as say City of Heroes.
<br />

<br />
As far as nothing to look forward to, yes it appears (to those that are impatient and post rather than read) that there is little to look forward to except increasing abilities of the same type.  However the developers have said they have every intention of adding new abilities as beta goes on, that they haven't gotten to it yet because they are trying to finish Hunters.  This is beta, not a finished product not everything has been implimented yet.
<br />

<br />
Lastly about &quot;uber&quot; equipment.  I think getting a double linked tunic (a rare item that drops off of a &quot;boss&quot; mobs) at level 31 is pretty d*mn uber.  The fact that there is better stuff out there that I will be unable to use for 8 or 10 levels means that I have to eventually upgrade my equipment.  That I need to go down to the bottom of another instanced dungeon with my friends and gather better equipment as we go.
<br />

<br />
I find the fact that I can have just as good equipment as someone who has a level 60 to be refreshing.  I find that when I kill a level 18 boss mob and get a piece of equipment that it is better to go WOW! and start using it than to think I wonder how much I can vendor this for.
<br />

<br />
Anyway, I am sorry you are not enjoying the game and hope that maybe EQ2 will be a better fit for you
<br />

<br />
Wrahn
<br />
Maestro, Impresario, Walker - Vazaelle</span></td>
