				<td colspan="2"><span>Praetor, at one point or another there is very standard gear in the EQ. All classes have their Elemental sets, and now GoD. The stats, focus effects, and damage/delay start to look all the same, varying only in combinations. Of course there are no distinguishable items in WoW sub-level cap...do you ever remember having uber_sword_06 at level 48 in EQ? I personally am not in the beta but have seen it in play; it seems like there is a much larger variety of things to do on WoW than what there is to do in EQ. Yet another point in WoW is that this is still in beta, and they still have not implemented the raid content. Unlike Sony, that pushes buggy content to almost an unplayable level (<a target="_new" href="http://fohguild.org/forums/showthread.php?s=b5faf650e835f7fe7fcd8aaa063956a6&amp;threadid=12084">http://fohguild.org/forums/showthread.php?s=b5faf650e835f7fe7fcd8aaa063956a6&amp;threadid=12084</a>), Blizzard is determined to release a high quality game with interesting content. They have more to release and I can say I am looking to sign up for the open beta <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-4.gif" border="0" alt="Tongue out" hspace="2" /></span></td>
