				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Just played WoW.<a name="57234"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 18 04 1:05 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">It is IMPOSSIBLE to own any equipment you could call &quot;uber&quot; at any level other than the max level. *ALL* items either have a min-level or are soulbound (no-drop). The min-levels are set such that at any given level (other than max level), you have only a handful of different gear choices, and they are all very similar in power. Staggeringly similar in power! For example, a very good staff for a level 15 will only be perhaps 5 dps better than a mediocre weapon. It's not possible to awe people with your great gear. Gear is inconsequential really.</span></blockquote>
<br />
You make the above statement as if it's a bad thing.  It's all a matter of perspective.  Level 15 warriors shouldn't be able to &quot;awe people with [their] great gear&quot; that would've taken a level 50 warrior with the assistance of well-balanced group to acquire without buying it.  
<br />

<br />
I firmly believe the first twinks and PLers were the ones that started the downturn in the quality of EQ, as people discovered ways to &quot;beat the system&quot; and level their toons at ridiculous speeds, without acquiring their gear themselves, and &quot;paying their dues.&quot;  People stopped being interested in experiencing the content in Norrath, concentrating only on leveling faster than the next guy...having better gear than the next guy...being able &quot;to awe people with [their] great gear.&quot;  
<br />

<br />
...and, once it became obvious that people were losing their interest in participating in the Norrath content, it was easy for the devs to justify not creating any <b><i>new</i></b> content, and just phoning it in with new expansions tailored toward the hard-core raiders.
<br />

<br />
Put me down as a &quot;yes&quot; vote.  It <b><i>should</i></b> be damned near impossible to have uber gear, if you're not an uber-level toon.
<br />

<br />
