				<td colspan="2"><span>I see lots of replies along the lines of &quot;we hate the ability to twink, so we're glad it's not possible in WoW.&quot;  Okay, I hear you.  And Blizzard heard you, and that's why they have the system they have.  It 100% destroys the ability to twink, and lots of people think that's a great idea.
<br />

<br />
At first, I did too.
<br />

<br />
But look at the ramifications.  Right now in EQ, you always have something new and great you can save for, no matter what level you are.  In WoW, you HAVE NO CHOICE but to take what is given to you via the quests for your current level (you can't even attempt quests meant for higher level people).  You MUST accept what gear they think is appropriate for your level.  This simplifies and abstracts gear to a point where it's almost a non-issue throughout the game.  I'm a fervent gear-collector, and I LOVE to dream of the next great item I can acquire.  In WoW, you never dream, because you know exactly what's coming up -- everyone else has the same thing, or something very comparable.
<br />

<br />
And this is all just to avoid some hardcore gamers from creating low-level toons with great gear?  I don't care if they do that, it doesn't bother me, it doesn't affect MY game at all.  I just want something to look forward to equipment-wise, and WoW doesn't allow that.
<br />
