			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Just played WoW.<a name="57326"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 18 04 12:08 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">I wouldn't write WoW off yet, give it a chance to actually finish beta, and have the end content found/explored. I would wager a bet it will be more than enough to look forward to.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
I would like nothing more than for you to be right.  However, end content doesn't matter to me.  I am the type of player that makes lots of characters up to mid-level, then starts over.  I have already done this during beta, and there are no mid-level raids, so all we have to look forward to is vendor loot, dropped items, and quest items.  They are all very similar, and not very interesting.
<br />

<br />
Just because EQ started a certain way 5 years ago, does not mean that that's the way all new MMORPGs have to start.  I think it's better to start right off the bat with a diverse array of equipment for players to choose from.  I hope that they will realize this and add more green/blue/purple items to the early and mid-game (levels 10-30).  There are lots of these items in the high-end game now, but that doesn't help people who don't have lots of time to play, or just like to play lots of characters.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
