				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Just played WoW.<a name="57332"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 18 04 12:17 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Very good point, I wasn't trying to say that EQ is the bible of MMOs, but just using it as a baseline comparison.
<br />

<br />
I would for the devs to add more content to the mid game, such a raids and encounters for large groups of people. In reality, only tehy know what is in store for WoW, as all of this could be in the works as we type, or it could not be.  These are some of the features that will make/break WoW for me as well.  I am not a hardcore, endgame player either.  But eventually we all get there and that is what keeps me playing the game is wanting to see zones that not everyone has seen and kill mobs that not everyone has killed.  THAT is a driving force in many games today, looking forward to new things.
<br />

<br />
WoW doesn't have that yet, but I will wait to &quot;say no to WoW&quot;.  Just as I will wait to try EQ2 until I have read many many reveiws of it.  I will most likely try both, the better of the two will keep me.</span></td>
